Are you preparing for it and are you able to adapt? Courtesy #DStv403 #Today JOHANNESBURG - 'Don't panic' seems to be the resounding message people receive when it comes to the COVID-19 outbreak. South Africa has closed the majority of its border posts following an increase in infections in the country. President Cyril Ramaphosa announced control measures for the viral outbreak on Sunday evening. Scenario planner and futurist, Graeme Codrington, says it's important to take precautionary measures. Codrington told eNCA, "we must not forget that about 90 percent of people will recover from the virus." EXPLAINER: How long can coronavirus survive on surfaces Scientists say a vaccine for COVID-19 could only be available in over a year. With up to 62 reported cases in South Africa, the reality is internal infections are likely to spread. Watch the full interview with Scenario planner and futurist, Graeme Codrington in the video above.  - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp.